<h1>Problem 2154 - 2025 RMM, P2 of 6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Consider an infinite sequence of positive integers \(a_1, a_2, a_3, \dots\) such that \(a_1 > 1\) and \((2^{a_n} - 1)a_{n+1}\) is a square for all positive integers \(n\). Is it possible for two terms of such a sequence to be equal?</p>
